headlines.description: — Collin Sexton scored 28 points, Darius Garland had 25 and the feisty Cleveland Cavaliers beat the East-best Philadelphia 76ers 112-109 in overtime on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Sexton, Garland help Cavaliers upset 76ers 112-109 in OT

headlines.description: — Bradley Beal scored 34 points, Russell Westbrook added 19 as part of his NBA-leading 10th triple-double, and the Washington Wizards used a 44-point third quarter to pull away for a 128-112 victory over the Minnesota Timberwolves on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wizards send Timberwolves to 7th straight loss, 128-112

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — DeMar DeRozan had 32 points and 11 assists and the short-handed San Antonio Spurs held on to beat the New Orleans Pelicans 117-114 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: DeMar DeRozan has 32 points, 11 assists in Spurs' victory

events.name: Indiana Pacers at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Julius Randle scored 28 points and grabbed 10 rebounds to lift the New York Knicks back to .500 with a 110-107 win over the Indiana Pacers on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Knicks outlast Pacers 110-107 behind Randle's double-double

headlines.description: — Donovan Mitchell scored 31 points and Joe Ingles filled in well again at point guard in place of Mike Conley to help the Utah Jazz beat the Orlando Magic 124-109 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: NBA-leading Jazz rebound from loss to beat Magic

events.name: Denver Nuggets at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: Jamal Murray continued his hot scoring with 26 points and Nikola Jokic had his eighth triple-double of the season to help the Denver Nuggets rout the Oklahoma City Thunder 126-96 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jamal Murray, Nikola Jokic help Nuggets rout Thunder 126-96

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic scored 27 points, Kristaps Porzingis added 18 in his return from injury and the Dallas Mavericks snapped the Brooklyn Nets' eight-game winning streak with a 115-98 victory Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mavs end Nets' 8-game run as Porzingis returns, Irving sits
